At the 16th China Charity Ranking on April 28 in Beijing, the "PepsiCo Nutrition In Action" program jointly launched by PepsiCo Greater China Region (GCR) and China Foundation for Poverty Alleviation (CFPA) received the honorable title of the "Charity Program for 2019," acknowledging the program's remarkable contribution to the escalation of the nutritious condition and the health awareness of the young students in the poverty-stricken areas in southwestern China.Since the China's Charity Ranking was first launched in 2004, it has established itself as a prominent list in the domestic charity sector for 16 consecutive years.Since December 2015, PepsiCo and CFPA collaboratively launched the "PepsiCo Nutrition In Action," aiming to provide poor students with eggs, milk and PepsiCo's Quaker oats nutrition meals that are rich in dietary fiber as well as organize nutritional health education courses to help improve nutrition and health awareness, and promote the healthy growth of teenagers in rural areas in western China's regions. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun